<TEXT>
two prison guards were hospitalized in good 
condition tuesday and three other guards and one inmate were 
treated for minor injuries and released after a 14hour 
hostagetaking ended in the early morning 
the handful of prisoners who had taken control of the 32inmate 
special housing unit at coxsackie correctional facility in greene 
county released the last four of the five guards about 1245 am 
tuesday 
i think they got tired said corrections commissioner thomas 
coughlin i think they felt very strongly that they were in over 
their heads after the initial assaults 
coughlin and gov mario cuomo told a state capitol news 
conference that they believed the incident which began about 1030 
am monday was an unorganized chain of events that escalated 
faster than the inmates intended 
what were dealing with is a mob coughlin said it was a 
bunch of young kids acting as a committee of 32 there was no 
planning there was no organization they knocked an officer down 
they took two other officers nightsticks and they said oh my 
god look what weve done now 
according to corrections department records the oldest inmate 
in the unit is 26 years old and most of the prisoners are in their 
upper teens or early 20s the prison 20 miles south of albany has 
951 inmates 
all the inmates remained locked in their cells tuesday 
according to corrections department spokesman james flateau 
coughlin said investigators hadnt determined how many inmates 
were involved in the uprising if those involved can be identified 
coughlin said he hoped they would be charged 
the inmates were armed with nightsticks he said 
officials have not determined the cause of the uprising but it 
started when an inmate overpowered guard lewis bloom in a 
recreation yard 
on monday flateau said some inmates had been complaining about 
verbal harassment by guards but cuomo said tuesday that the 
uprising was not a response to any specific incident 
guard david pratt 31 of coxsackie was in good condition 
tuesday with abdominal injuries at albany medical center hospital 
said hospital spokeswoman peggy pitcher a guard freed monday 
night warren agostinoni 28 of cairo was in good condition with 
cuts and bruises she said 
bloom and two other guards were released tuesday morning after 
treatment for bruises and cuts and an inmate was treated and 
released for chest and back injuries she said 
