<TEXT>
following are the major attacks this year in 
northern ireland england and europe blamed on guerrillas of the 
irish republican army 
jan 26 a policeman killed in belfast by an armorpiercing 
grenade that struck his armored patrol vehicle 
feb 29 two ulster defense regiment privates killed by a 
remotecontrolled bomb as they locked steel antiterrorist doors on 
royal avenue in belfasts main shopping area 
march 19 two british soldiers dragged from their car by 
mourners at an ira funeral then beaten unconscious with crowbars 
and shot to death 
may 1 three british airmen based in west germany killed and 
three wounded in two attacks in the netherlands a car bombing at 
nieuw bergen and a machinegun attack on a car near roermond 
may 5 a bomb attached to a british servicemans car in 
bielefeld west germany failed to explode 
may 21 a british soldier and his dog killed by a bomb blast 
while searching for explosives near the irish border 
may 29 a mortar attack on a military base at cookstown in 
county tyrone injured 14 soldiers and civilians none seriously 
june 15 a boobytrap bomb blasts a military vehicle in 
lisburn 7 miles southwest of belfast killing six british soldiers 
who had just competed in a charity race with about 4000 other 
people 
june 23 a british army helicopter made an emergency landing in 
south armagh near the irish border after what the ira said was its 
first attack using antiaircraft guns 
june 28 a bomb exploded in a school bus carrying 12 girls near 
enniskillen seriously injuring one girl and the driver who was a 
parttime member of the ulster defense regiment 
july 7 two civilians killed and 10 wounded at a swimming pool 
in west belfast by a bomb the ira said was triggered accidentally 
july 13 guerrillas cut through a fence at a british army base 
at duisberg west germany to plant two bombs that slightly injured 
nine soldiers 
july 23 a car bomb on the main dublinbelfast highway killed 
contractor robin hanna his wife maureen and 6yearold son david 
as they were returning from a vacation in the united states the 
ira said the bomb was meant for a northern ireland high court judge 
aug 1 one soldier killed and nine wounded by a bomb at the 
inglis barracks in north london 
</TEXT>
