linked school segregation to housing segregation for the first time 
the citys board of education launched its integration plan in 
1986 that same year sand ordered the city to construct 200 units 
of lowincome housing on the east side and 800 more units of 
housing throughout the city 160 lowincome homes and the rest for 
moderate incomes 
