pledged to fight the sand plan but in january under threat of 
fines the council agreed to a consent decree that would allow 
construction to go forward 
the public recoiled residents mobbed council meetings 
screaming for hours on end council members received bullets in the 
mail picket lines formed in front of the judges homes in 
manhattan and pound ridge 
the council flipflopped and sought to appeal the plan the 
us supreme court refused to hear the appeal but the council 
persisted in its opposition 
the threat of fines has special resonance in yonkers which 
required a state bailout to avoid bankruptcy in 1984 and has 
struggled to regain its financial footing the city has seen three 
years of budget surpluses as well as a growing tax base 
susan brewster executive director of the emergency financial 
control board established to monitor yonkers spending said if the 
city was found in contempt of court moodys investment co would 
suspend the citys baa bond rating such a move would jeopardize 
the citys financial future she said 
