<TEXT>
scientists using a 
oneperson submersible craft plan wednesday to make the first of 20 
dives looking for hot springs at the bottom of crater lake the 
deepest lake in the united states 
at a news conference on the lake rim national park service 
officials and researchers said they hope to confirm the existence 
of thermal vents on the lake bottom and gather data on many other 
features of the unusual body of water 
scientists began assembling gear for the unprecedented dive 
monday the submersible craft called deep rover and designed 
for ocean exploration was scheduled to be placed in the lake today 
the lake which resulted from the explosion of mount mazama 
nearly 7000 years ago is 1932 feet deep and is famous for its 
clear cobaltblue water 
the waters clarity is the main reason for the exploration of 
the lake which comes about halfway through a 10year study 
launched by congress in 1983 
scientists in the 1970s noticed that a small device used to 
measure the clarity of crater lake barely could be seen at 85 feet 
below the lakes surface before then the device frequently could 
be seen as deep as 115 feet 
scientists theorize vents below the lakes floor may be altering 
the clarity by stirring up sediment and plant life in the lake 
which has no inlets or outlets 
oregon state university researchers jack dymond and robert 
collier will take turns manning the submersible vessel on the 
dives they discovered small vents on the lake bottom last summer 
using a remote control diving device and say there is sufficient 
evidence to indicate the vents are hydrothermal that is the 
water coming from them is heated somehow 
dymond said it would require a remarkable coincidence of 
events to justify any other hypotheses because of the chemical 
differences found near the vents 
although the focus of the project is a search for geothermal 
activity the scientists are looking at it as a general study of 
the famous lake dymond said 
the lake has an incredible and complex volcanic glacial and 
explosive history he said 
officials said the major advantages of the deep rover which 
resembles a clear plastic bubble are its mobility and the 
exceptional visibility the operator has virtually 360 degrees 
extending arms on the device can be used to collect water samples 
and to probe into the vents 
dymond said it will allow the scientists to see crater walls 
below the surface that for the most part have never been observed 
before 
the exploration will be based on wizard island in the lake as a 
result the regular tour boat runs to the island have been 
suspended until the end of the project aug 28 
