<TEXT>
china is increasing its patrols of military ships 
and warplanes around the disputed spratly islands in the south 
china sea the official china daily newspaper reported wednesday 
last march chinese warships sank three vietnamese ships in a 
clash off the spratly chain that both countries claim the 
archipelago of hundreds of mostly uninhabited islands and reefs 
also is claimed by the philippines taiwan and malaysia but china 
and vietnam have engaged in hostilities over control 
the islands range from 300 miles southeast of the vietnamese 
mainland to 500700 miles south of chinas hainan island 
geological reports have indicated there could be large oil 
deposits in the area 
the china daily reported a senior naval officer who was not 
identified said training exercises around the spratly islands 
known in china as the nanshas are both offensive and defensive 
it quoted him as saying navy and air force warplanes have 
increased their maneuvers in coordination with navy ships to 
create a rapidresponse force 
since the march clash china has made public pronouncements and 
taken military measures to back up its claims to the islands 
navy officials said in june that the vietnamese had occupied 21 
islands in the archipelago and china was strengthening it forces to 
defend the islands 
they alsosaid at that time that an air traffic control center 
was being built on hainan to monitor international flights over the 
spratlys and also the disputed parcel islands 250 miles east of 
vietnam and 200 miles southeast of hainan 
chinas official xinhua news agency reported tuesday that a 
maritime observation station had been completed on yongshu reef at 
the southern end of the spratly islands 
it said the station was chinas first permanent base in the 
spratlys and was built at the request of the united nations 
educational scientific and cultural organization for the 
exploration of maritime resources 
