in the realm of television programming there 
is no such thing as a sure thing but if there was one it would 
probably be columbo 
after a decade off the air abc is bringing back peter falk as 
the beloved rumpled detective in a series of movies like other 
fall shows its debut has been delayed by the writers strike 
falk told a meeting of television critics that far from balking 
at a return to the small screen as columbo i never wanted it to 
go off in the first place 
it was always a problem to find out some way whereby from my 
point of view we could do a limited number of columbos and still 
do something else so i wouldnt spend my whole life doing this 
there were movies i wanted to do 
