<DOCNO> AP880802-0272 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a half century ago the russell clan left 
wall street for the much quieter avenues of tacoma today even 
though he keeps a minutebyminute watch on new york markets 
george russell has no desire to trade his view of puget sound for 
manhattan 
russell runs the frank russell group of companies named for 
his grandfather which advises pension funds and other large pools 
of capital on how to make the most money with the least risk 
clients include 40 of the largest us corporations among 
them international business machines corp general motors corp 
boeing co hearst corp and xerox corp plus a growing number of 
foreign companies foundations profitsharing plans and a few very 
rich individuals 
in all russell clients have holdings totaling about 240 
billion 
the 56yearold russell pioneered the idea of tracking 
performance of money managers so pension funds can rely on more 
than just intuition in deciding where to entrust their assets 
the privately held company now employs about 700 people and has 
annual revenues in the neighborhood of 100 million russell 
says 
hes proud of a new home office due to open in downtown tacoma 
this fall a telescope in his current headquarters lets visitors 
monitor the new buildings progress moreover hes proud the 
companys been able to make it in tacoma a city that suits his 
style 
i had a chance to go to wall street and didnt choose to get 
into that herdtype thoughtprocess he said 
if youre on wall street what youve got is a beeper on your 
belt and if you dont answer that beeper 24 hours a day youre 
not going to get your bonus at the end of the year 
we look at it quite differently and maybe its because were 
in tacoma i dont know but it seems to me that we ought to have 
the family beeper on the belt and if the family yells for help then 
the person ought to go solve that problem and then come do the 
business work 
in his line of work things will never improve unless the 
people that are in charge hire people that are smarter than they 
are russell said 
if you get the priorities in the right place to begin with as 
you run a business and you put the people ahead of the business 
then theyll eventually realize they can have fun in life too and 
the business will be fun too 
russells office reflects his workhardbuthavefun beliefs 
folding doors screen off a narrow walllength work area from the 
rest of the room which is filled with comfy furniture and 
photographs of his family the northwest and his 60foot yacht 
the boat he says has entertained a lot of clients if you 
come to new york you go out to a fine restauraunt in tacoma your 
options are different 
russell defines his outfit as asset management consultants 
three words that take him about 30 minutes to explain this is 
not an easy organization to understand he conceded 
besides advising the 40 corporate pension accounts the company 
gathers and sells statistics on money managers runs mutual funds 
for bank trust departments operates a brokerage house and offers 
investment funds and advice for smaller clients including 
endowments foundations and individuals 
it also has developed indexes for measuring stock and real 
estate performance including the russell 2000 and russell 3000 
indexes traded on the new york futures exchange 
if you think of a compass we pretty much on the consulting 
side are covering 360 degrees russell said 
doing so has brought his privately held company 25 percent 
growth in each of the past 15 years he says 
the staff hes put together has been helpful to us in deciding 
what we want to do in making investment decisions said al 
wolfarth assistant treasurer for pensions at monsanto corp which 
has used russell since 1974 in a field with many good companies 
wolfarth said i would refer to the russell firm as the cadillac 
of the industry 
russells grandfather frank started the company in 1936 when 
he retired as a merrill lynch broker to come to tacoma where his 
son was a newspaper executive he kept busy as an investment 
counselor and by running a small mutual fund 
all his friends were in it there were about 176 stockholders 
and 300000 in assets george russell said 
russell joined his grandfather when he graduated from harvard 
university in 1958 he took over the firm two months later when his 
grandfather died 
it prospered with about 300 salesmen by 1965 selling mutual 
funds life insurance and real estate syndication but the fact 
was that i didnt feel that we were adding any particular value 
