<TEXT>
the commerce department said tuesday it is 
easing restrictions on the export of lowerlevel computers and 
computerized equipment to china the soviet union and other eastern 
bloc countries 
the decision means that china will be permitted to buy computers 
with double the processing speed of those it previously has been 
allowed to purchase 
by eliminating the requirement that such exports be cleared by 
cocom the parisbased coordinating committee for multilateral 
export controls license processing should be cut by 50 days the 
department said 
this change is part of the united states objectives aimed at 
making the multilateral export control system stronger by focusing 
controls on truly strategic equipment and reducing unnecessary 
burdens imposed on industry commerce under secretary for export 
administration paul freedenberg said in a statement 
the new regulation also eases restrictions on the export of 
personal computers to those countries 
