<TEXT>
western union corp posted a 
299 million loss during its second quarter the company announced 
tuesday 
the latest loss compared to a loss of 990000 during the same 
period in 1987 
revenue during the quarter rose to 235 million from 2065 
million 
the telecommunications company lost 6282 million during the 
first six months of 1988 compared with a 198 million loss in the 
first half of 1987 due largely to restructuring charges of 603 
million in the first quarter resulting from western unions recent 
reorganization 
revenue during the sixmonth period rose to 4695 million from 
4111 million in the same period a year ago 
yearearlier figures do not include revenue from the former itt 
world communications inc which western union acquired dec 30 
including income from the business now known as worldcom revenue 
would have been 266 million in second quarter 1987 and 522 
million in the first half of last year 
following a series of unprofitable years western union 
completed a plan dec 30 to reorganize and move from providing 
communications facilities to providing specialized business and 
consumer services 
